      <hedline>
        <hl1>'In Defense of Elitism'</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Although it is so obvious one hates to take the bait, one is nevertheless forced to ask what William Henry and Roger Kimball -- upholders of "the ideal of disinterested judgment" -- make of George Eliot. Despite Mr. Kimball's protestations of how "painful" it is to admit certain "home truths," we should keep in mind exactly whose nose the bone is being shoved through.  JAY KAPLAN  New York</p>
      </block>
